  {
    "hotel_id": "178529",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/hotel-mystays-fukuoka-tenjin/hotel/fukuoka-jp.html",
    "name": "HOTEL MYSTAYS Fukuoka Tenjin",
    "detail": "The hotel is under the Hotel MyStays chain, which is just like the many other chains in Japan. As expected, rooms and bathrooms were small but clean and complete with all the necessary items to ensure a comfortable stay. The hotel is only a three-minute walk from the Tenjin Chikagai and Tenjin Station, and hence the entire city is easily accessible. Tenjin Station is only a few stops from Nakasu Kuwabata, Hakata and the Fukuoka Airport Stations. We did a day-trips to Hiroshima (via Shinkansen from Hakata Station) and Nagasaki (via bus from the Nishitetsu Bus Terminal), which were very easy to get to. The hotel's vicinity has countless restaurants, karaoke centers, drug stores, convenience stores and the traditional yatai at night. It is also within a five- to ten-minute walk to the Daimyo and Imaizumi neighborhood, which is probably the best shopping area in Fukuoka. Not to mention that Tenjin has a Parco, Mitsukoshi, Iwataya, Daimaru, Loft, Tenjin Core, Vivre, Aeon and many other shopping centers! Staff were, as with any other Japanese, extremely friendly and helpful. Would definitely stay in this hotel when in Fukuoka.",
